Objectives:
• To monitor trends in outbreaks of enteric, foodborne and waterborne diseases in Canada;
• To identify risk and contributing factors for outbreaks;
• To capture results of outbreak investigations in a systematic and standardized format;
• To share information, findings and experience with the Canadian Public Health community; and
• To evaluate Public Health interventions, in efforts to inform future outbreak investigations, policy developments, and outbreak prevention and control strategies.
